{
  "texts": [
    "Similarly, for p 0 > 0, j (I-II) (p) reduces to (a II pa I p).",
    "Thus, r.h.s.",
    "of (4.28) = ⟨0|C{ (b I k -a I k) (a II 1 ′ -a I 1 ′) (a II 2 ′ -a I 2 ′) (a † 1 I -a † 1 II) (a † 2 I -a † 2 II) }|0⟩, (4.30)where the C operation simply orders type-II operators to the left of type-I ones.",
    "As always, we work under the assumption that external momenta are not exactly forward, so we can JHEP01(2024)139 discard commutators between a's and a † 's.",
    "Hence, all but one term in (4.30) are trivial: all terms with a I vanish since they annihilate the vacuum on the right, and terms with a †II vanish since they annihilate the vacuum on the left."
  ]
}